This documentation describes the Guardtime Blockchain-enabled Service Broker for PCF. By using the Guardtime Blockchain-enabled Service Broker, applications and application service instances can sign data using Guardtime's Keyless Signature Infrastructure (KSI) that provides cryptographic signatures in real time.

The Guardtime Blockchain-enabled Service Broker registers a service broker on PCF and exposes the Guardtime Blockchain Services service on the Marketplace. Developers can create service instances of Guardtime Blockchain Services and bind them to their applications using Apps Manager or the cf Command Line Interface (CLI). Bound applications can sign and verify data using Guardtime KSI.

